# MuseLM v1

MuseLM is a lightweight decoder-only Transformer language model built from scratch in PyTorch. It includes a custom Byte Pair Encoding (BPE) tokenizer, a complete preprocessing pipeline, training scripts, and an interactive chat interface.

This project was created as a learning-focused implementation of a modern language model architecture and serves as the foundation for future versions of MuseLM.

---

## Features

* Decoder-only Transformer architecture
* Custom BPE tokenizer (16,000 vocabulary)
* Multi-head self-attention
* Pre-LayerNorm transformer blocks
* Weight tying between input embeddings and output layer
* AdamW optimizer with cosine learning rate scheduling
* Gradient clipping
* Automatic checkpoint saving
* Early stopping based on validation loss
* Interactive multi-turn chat interface

---

## Model Specifications

| Component           |                    Value |
| ------------------- | -----------------------: |
| Parameters          |             5.78 Million |
| Embedding Dimension |                      192 |
| Transformer Layers  |                        6 |
| Attention Heads     |                        8 |
| Context Length      |               128 Tokens |
| Vocabulary Size     |                   16,000 |
| Architecture        | Decoder-only Transformer |

---

## Training Data

MuseLM v1 was trained on conversational datasets including:

* UltraChat
* OpenAssistant (OASST)

Total training data:

* ~190 Million tokens

