---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/adityagahlan-lab/MuseLM.git
cd MuseLM

pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Training

After preprocessing the datasets:

```bash
python train.py
```

The best model is automatically saved as:

```
musellm.pt
```

Checkpoints are also saved periodically during training.

---

## Chat

Launch the interactive chat interface:

```bash
python chat.py
```

Example:

```
You: Hello
Bot: Hello! How can I help you today?
```

---

## Current Limitations

MuseLM v1 is an early research and learning project.

Current limitations include:

* Limited reasoning ability
* Conversation quality is inconsistent
* Sometimes generates unrelated responses
* Small context window (128 tokens)
* Small model size (5.8M parameters)

Future versions will improve conversation quality, context length, model capacity, and training data preprocessing.

---

## Future Roadmap

Planned improvements for MuseLM v2:

* Larger Transformer architecture
* Longer context window
* Improved preprocessing pipeline
* Better conversational formatting
* Stronger instruction following
* More efficient training

